<title>FRANCE: BIC 1997 Q1 sales up 13 percent.</title>
<headline>BIC 1997 Q1 sales up 13 percent.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>(All figures in millions of French francs)</p>
<p>    Turnover					 1,684    vs    1,491</p>
<p>     - BIC division				1,642    vs    1,389</p>
<p>     - Guy Laroche division			 42    vs	102</p>
<p>NOTE - BIC said in a statement its first-quarter sales rose 13 percent, or 10 percent on a like-for-like basis. The BIC division's sales rose 18 percent. Guy Laroche sales fell 59 percent.</p>
<p>BIC said acquisitions accounted for four percent of the total sales rise. It said the dollar averaged 5.60 francs in the first quarter of 1997, compared with 5.04 francs.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom +33 1 4221 5452</p>
